@endnode

@node "Prefs" "Prefs       "


   From this program you can setup this options:

  @{fg highlight}Global...@{fg text}

    Popup delay - Delay before popup 1 delay is 0.2 seconds.

    HotKey      - Hot key to popup window.(Use only valid Hotkeys,
                  otherwise program don't run.

    Screen      - RunBar popup screen.

    Control     - You can control Commodities&Windows, only Commodities or
                  only Windows.

    Border      - Window border type.
    
    Access menus time delay - Delay before open second menu.
                  1 delay is 0.1 second.
 
    12hour clock- You can select 12/24 clock system.

    Middle b.p. - If set you can use Middle mouse button as HotKey.
    
    Prefs Caching - Use prefs caching.

    Show Anim     - Anim on/off.

  @{fg highlight}Commodities...@{fg text}

    You can remove commodities from RunBar.

    Example: In my system I have commodity MultiCX and I don't want
             to see it in RunBar.Then, I add it to "skip list" and
             it makes not visible from RunBar.

    To add commdity here, simple add commodity name (like "MultiCX")
     to list.

    New         - Add new name.

    Remove      - Remove name from list.

  @{fg highlight}Prefs...@{fg text}

    You can skip Prefs from Prefs menu like commodities.

    Double click to first list to add Prefs to skip list.

    Double click to second list to remove item from skip list.

    Remember prefs position - Remember last prefs menu position.

    Prefs only with icons   - Show prefs only with icons.

  @{fg highlight}Utilities...@{fg text}

    You can add up to five your own Utilities in program.

    To add Utility press on checkbox, then you can input Utility
    name and select program.
 
  @{fg highlight}Layout...@{fg text}

    Images       - Images width selector.

    Font         - Menu font.

    Spacing      - Adding extra 2 point between items.

    Recessed     - Recessed items selection.

  @{fg highlight}Images...@{fg text}

    Width       - Images width.

    Height      - Images height.
   
    Load Images - Load Images from IFF ILBM file and convert it to RunBar
                  format with current selected width and height.
                  (Example file is included).

    View Images - View current images.
@endnode

@node "Exchange" "Exchange    "

  Using RunBar you can control programs like from standart WB
  Exchange program.


  Move mouse pointer to bottom of screen.RunBar window popup and
  if in your system exists some commodities you will can see buttons
  with commodity names.

  @{fg highlight}Operations with buttons...@{fg text}

    Press button - You send standart "Show Interface" to current program.

    Press and hold right mouse button over commodity button - Little
     command window popup from here you can select commands:

     Hide - Standart "Hide Interface" command.

     Activate/Deactivate - Standart Activate/Deactivate commands.

     Quit - Standart "Remove" command.
@endnode

@node "Support" "Support     "



  If you want make RunBar support in your program, you must know!!


  1) You must create Commodity port in your program.

  2) When you recive CXCMD_KILL you must quit from program.

  3) When you recive CXCMD_DISAPPEAR you must close all window
          and wait for CXCMD_APPEAR.(It possible to recive
          CXCMD_DISAPPEAR when your program is already hidden).

  4) When you recive CXCMD_APPEAR you must open all window.
          (It possible to recive CXCMD_APPEAR when your program is
          not hidden).
          If window already open, then you must Activate it and
          pop to front.

  5) CXCMD_DISABLE/CXCMD_ENABLE you can use as you want.
  
  6) If you want create RunBar plugins, see Develop dir for more info.
@endnode

@node "Programs" "Programs"


    Now RunBar have new feature - programs control port.
    
    In archive included two programs FilterControl and CpuControl.
    
    When you run this programs, around RunBar clock you can see small
    pictures, press and hold right mouse button over it. Now select
    needed function and release right mouse button.
    
    If you want support that RunBar feature in your program, see Develop
    dir for more info.
@endnode

